  "prompt": "Is there an Android application that I can use to lookup words anywhere on my phone, without needing to have the application opened?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several Android applications that allow you to look up words anywhere on your phone without needing to have the app open. Here are a few popular options:\n\n1. **Google Translate**: Google Translate has a feature called \"Tap to Translate,\" which lets you highlight text in any app and translate it by tapping the floating icon. You can enable this feature in the app's settings.\n\n2. **Dictionary.com**: Dictionary.com has a feature called \"Floating Dictionary\" which can be enabled in the settings. It allows you to highlight text and access definitions without having to switch apps.\n\n3. **WordLookup**: This app allows you to highlight any text on your screen and get definitions or translations instantly. It runs in the background and can be accessed through a floating icon.\n\n4. **ColorDict**: This dictionary app allows you to highlight words in any app and get quick definitions. You can set it up to work with various dictionary sources.\n\n5. **Floating Dictionary**: Similar to the above, this app provides you with a floating window to look up definitions or translations of words by simply selecting them.\n\nTo use these apps effectively, you may need to enable permissions for overlay or accessibility, depending on the app's requirements. Make sure to check the app's settings for customization options to suit your preferences.",
